name: Zelda (Twilight Princess)
description:
HIGHLY RECOMMENDED: https://civitai.com/models/7808/easynegative

Alright got the first Zelda working. I started with Twilight Princess because of the three easy ones she had the least stopping me. BoTW already sort of has one so that was out for now. ALttP/ALBW is my favorite so it will be last meaning it was also out. Speaking of other Zeldas, who should be next?

As Usual:
Trained on Anything v3
Demos are Anything v4.5 with 0.8 weight
Last three images use my other LoRAs at 0.8:
aaaa, metata, Harada Takehito

modelVersions.description:
Whoops.... I really wanted a general Zelda LoRA that could do them all but instead got one that can't accurately do any.

Who are those last two:
Accidental random elf girls.

Stuff that is technically in the LoRA even if you can't get to it:

Games:
loz (original) very hard
((loz)), ((brown hair)), short hair, pink dress
botw easy
botw, blue shirt, black legwear, leggings, black pants
sksw very hard
(SkSw:2.5), sidelocks, white dress, blunt bangs, hair ribbon
(braid:1.5) in the negatives
sptr/tww yeah right
(sptr:1.4), (tww:1.4), toon zelda
twpr doable-ish
(twpr:1.4), (brown hair:1.4), dress, tabard, (purple tabard:1.4), tiara
(braid:1.5) in the negatives
alttp/albw
(albw:1.4), pink dress, circlet, tabard, pink tabard, blue eyes, blonde hair
(braid:1.5) in the negatives
totk easy
botw, totk, short hair, blue shirt, black legwear, leggings, black pants
hywa (didn't even try)
oot (didn't even try)
majm (didn't even try)

Zeldas:
princess zelda (default)
young zelda (from that one game but no shot it works)
toon zelda (technically there but not make able)
